summary: Right, so i know I'm just an art blog but I'm feeling v soft today and i wanted to talk( type?) about d&p for a sec. I’ve been...
body:
Right, so i know I’m just an art blog but I’m feeling v soft today and i wanted to talk( type?) about d&p for a sec. I’ve been in the Phandom for about a year now and at about the same time I was diagnosed with clinical depression, but the impact that these two dorks have had on me is wonderful. Whenever I’m having a depressy day or start getting anxious(panic attack), I just watch one of their videos or cuddle with my d&p plushies. I don’t even have to see the video, just hearing their voices and dumb jokes just gives me this overwhelming feeling of comfort.

And then there’s Dan’s video on his depression. I had been putting off watching it because I didn’t know if it would make things worse (my life was pretty shit at the time) or if i would be disapointed(as if). When i finally watched it, it made me feel as if i wasnt alone and gave me awnsers to questions i didnt even know i had. He reminded me to take care of myself and hearing about his experience made me feel so much better about my situation.

Don’t even get me started on Phil, he’s just so positive and “weird”, the very things I was made fun of in school. I had stopped being myself because I wanted to fit in and not be judged/made fun of( and because of depression). But he reminded me to just be myself and to embrace my weird quality’s and strange array of animal facts. The fact that there was not only someone so sucsesful but someone that i looked up to, that is just as weird as me, makes me feel some much better about being myself.Even though ive never even meet these men, they still have the power to make me feel so unbelivably happy and i am so grateful to them. :)

So that was my lil rant im sorry but i had a shit day yesterday so I spent the entire day watching D&P in my dank blankie cave lmao. Well bye, you are all better than toast!

-Cathy
